  {
    "id": "a498769e7465f7c9817fb99dcc8868b6",
    "title": "Don’t Lose the Democratizing Effect of Remote Work",
    "domain": "hbr.org",
    "url": "https://hbr.org/2021/08/dont-lose-the-democratizing-effect-of-remote-work",
    "text": "url: https://hbr.org/2021/08/dont-lose-the-democratizing-effect-of-remote-work\ntitle: Don’t Lose the Democratizing Effect of Remote Work\ndomain: hbr.org\ncategory: newwork\ndate_scanned: 2026-03-01T09:50:26.870490\nword_count: 219\npaywall: False\n---\n\n# Don’t Lose the Democratizing Effect of Remote Work\n\n\n\n\n\n\n---\n\nHarvard Business Review Logo\n\nEmployee retention\n\nDon’t Lose the Democratizing Effect of Remote Work\n\nby\n\nJoan C. Williams\n\n,\n\nRachel M. Korn\n\nand\n\nMikayla Boginsky\n\nAugust 4, 2021\n\nHBR Staff/James Barr/Dale Alejandro/Prince Akachi/Stocksy\n\nPost\n\nPost\n\nShare\n\nSave\n\nBuy Copies\n\nPrint\n\nSummary\n\n.\n\nLeer en español\n\nLer em português\n\nPost\n\nPost\n\nShare\n\nSave\n\nBuy Copies\n\nPrint\n\nPeople are calling it “\n\nthe big quit\n\n.” Employees are leaving workplaces that don’t suit their needs anymore, as more and more organizations return to in-person work after more than a year of working remotely. Half of workers now report that they will not return to\n\njobs that do not offer remote work\n\n.\n\nJoan C. Williams\n\nis director of the Equality Action Center and author of\n\nBias Interrupted: Creating Inclusion for Real and for Good\n\n(HBR Press) and\n\nOutclassed: How the Left Lost the Middle Class and How to Win Them Back\n\n(forthcoming, May 2025, St. Martin’s).\n\nRachel M. Korn\n\nis the research director at Equality Action Center, University of California College of the Law, San Francisco.\n\nMikayla Boginsky\n\nis the policy and research fellow at the Center for WorkLife Law University of California, Hastings Law.\n\nPost\n\nPost\n\nShare\n\nSave\n\nBuy Copies\n\nPrint\n\nRead more on\n\nEmployee retention\n\nor related topics\n\nGender\n\n,\n\nRace\n\n,\n\nRemote work\n\n,\n\nTalent management\n\nand\n\nDisabilities"
  },
